| Plot                    = Following the events of ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', Natasha Romanoff finds herself alone and forced to confront a dangerous conspiracy with ties to her past. Pursued by a force that will stop at nothing to bring her down, Romanoff must deal with her history as a spy and the broken relationships left in her wake long before she became an [[Avengers (Earth-199999)|Avenger]].{{cite|ref=true|url=https://comicbook.com/marvel/2020/01/14/marvel-black-widow-movie-synopsis-story-details/ |title=Marvel Releases New Black Widow Synopsis |last=Outlaw |first=Kofi |date=January 14, 2020 |website=ComicBook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115170045/https://comicbook.com/marvel/2020/01/14/marvel-black-widow-movie-synopsis-story-details/ |archive-date=February 11, 2020 |access-date=February 11, 2020}}

| Cast                    = * {{WP|Scarlett Johansson}} as [[Natalia Romanoff (Earth-199999)|Black Widow / Natasha Romanoff]]{{cite|ref=true|refname=SDCC 2019|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/movies/sdcc-2019-all-of-the-marvel-studios-news-coming-out-of-hall-h-at-san-diego-comic-con|title=SDCC 2019: All of the Marvel Studios News Coming Out of Hall H at San Diego Comic-Con|author=Marvel|work=Marvel.com|date=July 20, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019}}
