* {{WP|Ray Winstone}} as [[General Dreykov (Earth-199999)|General Dreykov]]{{cite|ref=true|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/black-widow-marvel-ray-winstone-1203249397/|title=Ray Winstone Joins Marvel's 'Black Widow' (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Kroll|first=Justin|work=Variety|date=June, 20 2019|accessdate=July 20, 2019}}{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a31910083/black-widow-ray-winstone-dreykov/|title=Black Widow reveals Ray Winstone's key role|last=Edwards|first=Chris|work=Digital Spy|date=March 24, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}
* {{WP|Olivier Richters}} as [[Mikhail Ursus (Earth-199999)|Ursa / Mikhail Ursus]]{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B1Ed9YGl9MK/|title=MARVEL 🤩!!!|name=Richters|first=Olivier|work=Instagram|date=August 12, 2019|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}

Additionally, {{WP|Julia Louis-Dreyfus}} makes an uncredited appearance as [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine (Earth-199999)|Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] in the film's post-credits scene, a role originally intended to debut in this film, before in the Disney+ series {{sl|The Falcon and The Winter Soldier}}.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2021/04/julia-louis-dreyfus-marvel-villain-character-contessa-valentina-allegra-de-fontaine|title=Marvel Has Big Plans for That Surprise Falcon and the Winter Soldier Cameo|last= Robinson|first=Joanna|work=Vanity Fair|date=April 16, 2021|accessdate=April 16, 2021}} Also, {{WP|Jeremy Renner}} has an uncredited cameo, he voiced [[Clinton Barton (Earth-199999)|Clint Barton]] in a flashback scene.<ref>https://screenrant.com/black-widow-easter-eggs-mcu-marvel-references-secrets/</ref>

| Notes                   = * This film has had multiple changes to its US release date due to the {{WP|COVID-19 pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic}}:
** Originally slated to be released on May 1, 2020 in the US, the release was pulled on March 17, 2020.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://variety.com/2020/film/box-office/black-widow-release-coronavirus-1203532996/|title= ‘Black Widow’ Release Pulled Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|work= Variety|last= Rubin|first= Rebecca|date= March 17, 2020|accessdate= March 17, 2020}} On April 3, 2020, it was announced that the release date for this film had been pushed to November 6, 2020.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://variety.com/2020/film/box-office/disney-mulan-black-widow-release-dates-coronavirus-1203550173/|title= ‘Black Widow,’ ‘Eternals,’ ‘Indiana Jones 5’ and More Disney Films Get New Release Dates|work= Variety|last= Rubin|first= Rebecca|date= April 3, 2020|accessdate= April 3, 2020}} 
** In September 2020, the film was pushed back again to May 7, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/black-widow-west-side-story-eternals-release-date-delay-1234773491/|title=‘Black Widow,’ ‘West Side Story,’ ‘Eternals’ Postpone Release Dates|accessdate=September 24, 2020|last=Lang|first=Brent|coauthors=Rubin, Rebecca|date=September 23, 2020|work=Variety}}
** In March 2021, the film was pushed back for a third time to July 9, 2021, releasing in theaters and on Disney+ with Premier Access on the same day.<ref name="Twitter">[https://twitter.com/MarvelStudios/status/1374429041877389320 Black Widow in theaters July 9, 2021]</ref>
* This was originally intended to be the Marvel Studios property that launched Phase 4 of their [[Earth-199999|cinematic universe]]. However, due to the film's release date delays, the Disney+ series ''[[WandaVision]]'' began Phase 4 instead, with ''Black Widow'' instead being slated as the first film of Phase 4.

